## Asymmetries (per MP.1 known_asymmetries; authoritative per `CANONICAL_ARTIFACTS_v1_0.md §2`)

Claude-side files and Gemini-side files each contain agent-specific constructs without a counterpart on the other side. The mirror does **not** synthesize fake counterparts.

- **Claude-only, no Gemini mirror:**
  - `CLAUDE.md` Claude Code / MCP server / skills references (CLI-tool integration; product-specific feature of the Claude Code environment with no Gemini equivalent).
  - `CLAUDE.md` `<system-reminder>`-style anchored prompt conventions and Claude-tool expectations.
  - `00_ARCHITECTURE/GOVERNANCE_STACK_v1_0.md` — declared Claude-only at MP.6.
  - `00_ARCHITECTURE/SESSION_LOG.md` — declared Claude-only at MP.7 (session history authored by Claude sessions; Gemini state reflected via MP.2 composite, not a separate Gemini log).
  - `00_ARCHITECTURE/CANONICAL_ARTIFACTS_v1_0.md` itself — Claude-resident; this file cites it by reference rather than duplicating content.
  - `00_ARCHITECTURE/STEP_BRIEFS/` — per-step briefs are Claude-resident; Gemini sessions read but do not author.
- **Gemini-only, no Claude mirror:**
  - `.geminirules` Gemini-rules idiom and "Gemini's Specific Role in L4" addressing pattern — addressed at this agent.
  - `.gemini/project_state.md` state-pointer file — adapted format for Gemini's construct; Claude-side equivalent is the composite of SESSION_LOG + STEP_LEDGER + active plan pointers (MP.2 composite).

These asymmetries are tracked per-pair in `CANONICAL_ARTIFACTS_v1_0.md §2 known_asymmetries`. Drift between this aggregate declaration and per-pair declarations is itself a finding (class `asymmetry_declaration_drift`) caught by `mirror_enforcer.py`.

Follow these principles rigorously.

